# Portfólio EDU — project conventions

## Stack
- Main site: vanilla HTML/CSS/JS (no bundler). Deploy via GitHub Pages at `cardoso-ix.github.io/Portifolio/`.
- Scripts: Python 3 (`Pillow`, `ReportLab`) in `scripts/`.
- Embedded sub-app: `conversor-unidades/` is a pre-built Vite artifact — do not edit hashed files; rebuild from source repo.

## Content tone
- Portuguese (pt-BR). Public positioning: **universal professional identity** — tech support + AI/automation (n8n, OpenAI, APIs). Never freela/pacotes.
- **Facts only:** education, companies, titles and dates must match `scripts/generate_cv.py` / the CV PDF. Never invent schools (e.g. UNOESC) or employers.
- Adapt tone for Help Desk N1/N2 + n8n without inventing tools, metrics or roles. Framing ≠ fabrication.
- Do **not** put job-hunting language in the public envelope (hero, headline, meta): avoid “busco vaga”, “CLT”, “aberto a vagas”, “não freela”.
- Lead with characteristics and proof (projects + real Help Desk at Crescer Sistemas). CTAs: projetos, currículo, contato.
- Do **not** lead with metrologia/calibração; Help Desk experience may be highlighted as support proof.
- Pós Tech / RAG / CrewAI stay as “estudando”, not the hero pitch.
- Keep `docs/LINKEDIN-PERFIL.md` and `docs/AVALIACAO-PERFIL.md` aligned when public positioning changes.

## CSS
- Use existing CSS custom properties in `:root` / `[data-theme="light"]` (graphite + muted olive; avoid AI-blue / neon cyan/magenta).
- Keep layout centered (`--container-width: 88rem`) with one featured project + compact project grid.
- Prefer a clean layout: no particle canvas, no background grid, minimal glow; no “Atuação/serviços” section.
- BEM-like naming: `.section__element`, `.block__element--modifier`.
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce` for animations.

## JS
- Keep `main.js` as a single IIFE with `'use strict'`.
- Use passive scroll listeners and `requestAnimationFrame` throttling.
- Bump `?v=` query on `css/style.css`, `js/main.js`, and PDF links when shipping cache-sensitive assets.

## CV generator
- `scripts/generate_cv.py` writes to paths relative to `ROOT` (project folder).
- After editing CV data, run `python scripts/generate_cv.py` and commit `assets/cv_eduardo_cardoso.pdf`.

## Paths
- GitHub Pages base path is `/Portifolio/` — subproject links must account for this.
- Repo remote: `cardoso-ix/Portifolio` (local folder may be `Portifolio-EDU`).
